72
00:06:54,840 --> 00:06:59,340
So it's becoming very common in Melbourne.

73
00:06:59,340 --> 00:07:00,120
Thank you.

74
00:07:00,120 --> 00:07:03,440
How do you become a part of that process?

75
00:07:03,440 --> 00:07:05,960
How do you become a participant in a process?

76
00:07:05,960 --> 00:07:07,160
Yes, a participant.

77
00:07:08,340 --> 00:07:11,500
You are randomly sampled of a database.

78
00:07:11,500 --> 00:07:23,400
And then once people have expressed interest, so you might hope that you get three or four hundred people to express interest, and then they are selected again to match the demographics of the area in which you are.

79
00:07:23,400 --> 00:07:25,800
So it's actually random, stratified random.

80
00:07:25,800 --> 00:07:27,920
So you can express your interest?

81
00:07:27,920 --> 00:07:32,460
Only if you, well, there are a couple of different methods of, it's called sortition.

82
00:07:32,460 --> 00:07:34,620
There are a couple of different methods for doing it.

83
00:07:34,660 --> 00:07:37,740
One is where a physical invitation goes out.

84
00:07:37,740 --> 00:07:42,120
Only those people who got the invitation can express interest, and that will be checked.

85
00:07:42,120 --> 00:07:43,440
You know, your address is checked.

86
00:07:43,860 --> 00:08:08,160
There's a second method that some people are using where you go out and you let absolutely everyone, you know, you just put ads out, you do social media, but you need to get hundreds and hundreds of people under that method to make sure you get the randomness in the next step when you're selecting, because you've got to make sure you get randomness rather than just the usual people who turn up all the time.

87
00:08:08,160 --> 00:08:10,380
What is this database that you mentioned?

88
00:08:10,900 --> 00:08:13,860
The most typical one used is Australia Post.

89
00:08:13,860 --> 00:08:16,000
It's an Australia Post database.

90
00:08:17,160 --> 00:08:18,380
There are others used.

91
00:08:18,380 --> 00:08:30,040
